<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>{% block title %}Mimi — the media monitoring tool{% endblock %}</title>
<style>
  :root {
    --ink: #1a1a1a; --ink-soft: #4a4a4a; --ink-faint: #7a7a72;
    --paper: #fbfaf7; --field: #ffffff; --rule: #ddd9d0; --rule-ink: #1a1a1a;
    --accent: #1a1a1a; --error-bg: #f7e9e6; --error-border: #c9a59c; --error-ink: #7a2e22;
    --ok-bg: #eaf1e8; --ok-border: #a9c3a0; --note-bg: #f4f1ea; --card-bg: #fdfcfa;
    --warn-bg: #f9f2e7; --warn-border: #d9c6a0;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  html { font-size: 17px; }
  body { margin: 0; background: var(--paper); color: var(--ink);
    font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", Times, serif; line-height: 1.5;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; }
  .sheet { max-width: 44rem; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2.4rem 1.4rem 4rem; }
  .smallcaps { text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.13em; font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--ink-soft); }

  header.masthead { text-align: center; border-bottom: 4px double var(--rule-ink);
    padding-bottom: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0; }
  header.masthead h1 { margin: 0 0 0.3rem; font-size: 2.3rem; font-weight: 700; }
  header.masthead p { margin: 0; font-style: italic; color: var(--ink-faint); }

  /* Newspaper-style section nav: shared across the editor and report views. */
  .section-nav { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; gap: 0.3rem 1.25rem;
    padding: 0.45rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); margin-bottom: 1.7rem; }
  .new-report-btn { font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 0.72rem; text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-weight: 700; color: var(--paper); background: var(--accent);
    padding: 0.45em 0.9em; border-radius: 3px; text-decoration: none; white-space: nowrap; }
  .new-report-btn:hover { background: #000; }
  .nav-empty { font-style: italic; font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--ink-faint); }
  .nav-section { position: relative; }
  .nav-section > .nav-section-name { display: inline-block; font-family: Georgia, serif;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.09em; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--ink);
    padding: 0.35rem 0.1rem; cursor: default; border-bottom: 2px solid transparent; }
  .nav-section:hover > .nav-section-name, .nav-section:focus-within > .nav-section-name {
    border-bottom-color: var(--rule-ink); }
  .nav-dropdown { position: absolute; top: 100%; left: 0; z-index: 5; min-width: 8rem;
    background: var(--field); border: 1px solid var(--rule); border-radius: 3px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 14px rgba(0,0,0,0.09); padding: 0.25rem 0; display: none; }
  .nav-section:hover > .nav-dropdown, .nav-section:focus-within > .nav-dropdown { display: block; }
  .nav-dropdown a, .nav-dropdown button { display: block; width: 100%; text-align: left;
    font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--ink); background: none; border: none;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.9rem; text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; }
  .nav-dropdown a:hover, .nav-dropdown button:hover { background: var(--note-bg); }
  .nav-dropdown form { margin: 0; }

  /* Info button + modal */
  .info-btn { font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 0.72rem; text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-weight: 700; color: var(--ink); background: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-ink); padding: 0.4em 0.85em; border-radius: 3px; cursor: pointer; white-space: nowrap; }
  .info-btn:hover { background: var(--note-bg); }
  #info-modal { display: none; position: fixed; inset: 0; z-index: 30; background: rgba(26,26,26,0.42);
    padding: 2rem 1rem; overflow-y: auto; }
  #info-modal.open { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: center; }
  .info-panel { background: var(--paper); max-width: 40rem; width: 100%; margin: auto; border-radius: 5px;
    box-shadow: 0 12px 44px rgba(0,0,0,0.28); padding: 1.5rem 1.6rem 1.8rem; }
  .info-head { display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--rule-ink); padding-bottom: 0.6rem; margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
  .info-head h2 { margin: 0; font-size: 1.5rem; }
  .info-close { font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.7rem; line-height: 1; color: var(--ink-soft);
    background: none; border: none; cursor: pointer; padding: 0 0.2rem; }
  .info-close:hover { color: var(--ink); }
  .info-box { background: var(--note-bg); border-radius: 3px; padding: 0.9rem 1.15rem; margin-bottom: 1.1rem; }
  .info-box:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .info-box h3 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 1.02rem; }
  .info-box ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.1rem; }
  .info-box li, .info-box p { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.55; margin: 0.35rem 0; }
  .info-box p:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .info-box p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .info-box strong { color: var(--ink); }
  .info-box code { font-style: normal; font-size: 0.8rem; }

  /* Toast: transient save confirmation, bottom-right. */
  .toast { position: fixed; bottom: 1.3rem; right: 1.3rem; z-index: 40; max-width: 24rem;
    background: var(--ok-bg); border: 1px solid var(--ok-border); color: #2f5227;
    padding: 0.8rem 1.1rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.45;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.16); }
  @media (max-width: 34rem) { .toast { left: 1.3rem; right: 1.3rem; max-width: none; } }

  {% block extra_css %}{% endblock %}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="sheet">

  <header class="masthead">
    <h1>Mimi, the media monitoring tool</h1>
    <p>An open-source project for building reports on US and UK headlines.</p>
    <p>Developed by Ziad Ramley.</p>
  </header>

  <nav class="section-nav">
    <button type="button" class="info-btn" onclick="openInfo()">Info</button>
    <a class="new-report-btn" href="/?new=1" onclick="return confirmNew();">New report</a>
    {% for s in saved_searches %}
    <div class="nav-section" tabindex="0">
      <span class="nav-section-name">{{ s.name }}</span>
      <div class="nav-dropdown">
        <a href="/run/{{ s.slug }}">Run</a>
        <a href="/edit/{{ s.slug }}">Edit</a>
        <form class="delete-form" method="post" action="/delete/{{ s.slug }}" data-name="{{ s.name }}">
          <button type="submit">Delete</button>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
    {% if not saved_searches %}<span class="nav-empty">Saved reports will appear here.</span>{% endif %}
  </nav>

  {% block content %}{% endblock %}

</div>

{% if flash %}<div class="toast" id="toast">{{ flash }}</div>{% endif %}

<div id="info-modal" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="info-title">
  <div class="info-panel">
    <div class="info-head">
      <h2 id="info-title">About Mimi</h2>
      <button type="button" class="info-close" onclick="closeInfo()" aria-label="Close">&times;</button>
    </div>

    <div class="info-box">
      <h3>How to use Mimi</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>How it works:</strong> Mimi pulls headlines via RSS from a network of US and UK news outlets.</li>
        <li><strong>Building reports:</strong> Reports are made up of queries. You can have a single query or consolidate multiple into one report.</li>
        <li><strong>Saving reports:</strong> Save a report to run it again without re-entering details.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="info-box">
      <h3>Terms of use</h3>
      <p>Mimi is free, open-source software provided under the MIT License, “as is” and without warranty of any kind.</p>
      <p>Mimi collects only what outlets publish in their public RSS feeds — headlines, summaries, bylines, timestamps, and links. That content belongs to the publishers and remains subject to each publisher’s own terms. Mimi does not access or store full article text; read full articles through your own subscriptions.</p>
      <p>You are responsible for using Mimi in line with the terms of the outlets you monitor, and for how you use the reports it produces.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="info-box">
      <h3>Privacy policy</h3>
      <p>Mimi runs entirely on your own machine. There is no account, no server, and no analytics or tracking.</p>
      <p>The only network requests Mimi makes are to fetch the public RSS feeds you have chosen, directly from the publishers. Nothing you type — your queries, report names, or saved reports — is ever sent anywhere.</p>
      <p>Saved reports and generated reports are stored as ordinary files on your computer, in the <code>searches/</code> and <code>reports/</code> folders. They stay there until you delete them.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

{% block overlay %}{% endblock %}

<script>
  // Info modal (how-to, terms, privacy).
  function openInfo() { document.getElementById("info-modal").classList.add("open"); }
  function closeInfo() { document.getElementById("info-modal").classList.remove("open"); }
  document.getElementById("info-modal").addEventListener("click", function (e) {
    if (e.target === this) closeInfo();  // click on the backdrop closes
  });
  document.addEventListener("keydown", function (e) {
    if (e.key === "Escape") closeInfo();
  });

  // "New report" confirmation.
  function confirmNew() {
    return confirm("Clear everything and start a new report? Anything you haven’t saved will be lost.");
  }

  // Confirm deletes. The name is read from a data- attribute (a safe HTML
  // attribute context) rather than interpolated into inline JS — so a saved
  // report named with quotes or script can't execute here.
  document.querySelectorAll(".delete-form").forEach(function (form) {
    form.addEventListener("submit", function (e) {
      var name = form.dataset.name || "this report";
      if (!confirm("Delete the saved report “" + name + "”?")) e.preventDefault();
    });
  });

  // Auto-dismiss the save-confirmation toast after 5 seconds.
  var toast = document.getElementById("toast");
  if (toast) {
    setTimeout(function () {
      toast.style.transition = "opacity 0.6s";
      toast.style.opacity = "0";
      setTimeout(function () { toast.remove(); }, 600);
    }, 5000);
  }
</script>
{% block extra_js %}{% endblock %}
</body>
</html>
